@page "/privacy-policy"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.AllowAnonymous]

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy &mdash; Sports Club</PageTitle>

<div class="static-page">
    <div class="page-header">
        <div class="page-header-inner">
            <span class="page-eyebrow">Legal</span>
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="page-subtitle">How we collect, use, and protect your personal data. Last updated: June 2025.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="static-content">
        <div class="static-inner">
            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
                <p>
                    Sports Club Event Manager (&ldquo;the Club&rdquo;) is the data controller responsible for your personal data
                    in accordance with Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (GDPR) and Spanish Organic Law 3/2018 (LOPDGDD).
                </p>
                <p>
                    Contact: <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> &mdash; Email: privacy@sportsclub.example
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
                <p>We may collect and process the following personal data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Identity data:</strong> name, surname, member identifier.</li>
                    <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> email address, phone number.</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> event registrations, cancellations, session history.</li>
                    <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, pages visited (collected via logs).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>3. Purpose and Legal Basis</h2>
                <p>We process your data to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Manage your membership and event registrations (legitimate interest / contractual necessity).</li>
                    <li>Send notifications about events you have registered for (legitimate interest).</li>
                    <li>Comply with legal obligations applicable to sports associations in Spain.</li>
                    <li>Improve and maintain the platform (legitimate interest).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
                <p>
                    Your personal data is retained for as long as your membership is active and for up to five (5) years
                    after the end of the membership relationship, in accordance with Spanish civil and tax legislation.
                    Technical logs are retained for a maximum of twelve (12) months.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>
                    We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. Data may be shared with:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Hosting and infrastructure providers acting as data processors under a data processing agreement.</li>
                    <li>Public authorities when required by law.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>Under GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Access</strong> your personal data.</li>
                    <li><strong>Rectify</strong> inaccurate data.</li>
                    <li><strong>Erasure</strong> (&ldquo;right to be forgotten&rdquo;).</li>
                    <li><strong>Restrict</strong> processing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Data portability</strong> in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
                    <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing based on legitimate interest.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="/contact">our contact page</a>. You also have the right
                    to lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Authority (AEPD) at <strong>www.aepd.es</strong>.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>7. Cookie Use</h2>
                <p>
                    We use cookies and similar technologies. For full details, please refer to our <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="static-section">
                <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Material changes will be communicated to members via email
                    or a prominent notice on the platform. Continued use of the platform after notification constitutes
                    acceptance of the updated policy.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <em>Note: This privacy policy is a template and must be reviewed by qualified legal counsel before publication.</em>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
